The paper deals with transferring styles from existing maps or visual art to new maps using generative adversarial networks (GANs). This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered under the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multiscale features and the importance of preserving them during style transfer, which falls under the cs.GR sub-category. Additionally, the use of AI technologies such as GANs and deep learning is a common theme in the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also discusses the training and optimization of the GAN model, which is a topic covered under the cs.LG sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the generation of new maps, which is a topic covered under the cs.MM sub-category.
